Standard Bank and Capitec have confirmed that they will be hiking banking fees in line with the new VAT increase to 15%. The changes will take effect from 1 April 2018. Standard Bank has published an updated fee schedule on its website, while Capitec too has publish a flier notifying customers of the changes. Below are the changes to Standard Bank’s fees for its mid-market Elite Banking account, and Capitec’s Global One account, for a selection of common transactions. In line with the VAT hike, most prices have increased by approximately 1%.